THE MIRROR ANALOGY: DECIDE TO SMILE FIRST

The Glass Mirror Principle

• Physical reality is very much like a glass mirror
• If you look in a mirror and see your reflection frowning, you don't go to the mirror and try to make the reflection smile
• You know the only way to get the reflection to smile is to decide to smile first
• When you do, the reflection has no choice but to smile back

The Illusion of Changing Outer Reality

• Many attempt to change things in their lives by changing the outward ideas - this is an illusion
• This is what humans call "the cart before the horse"
• You cannot change reality by trying to manipulate the reflection
• You must change yourself first, then the reflection changes

Understanding Space-Time Lag

• Physical reality has a kind of density to it
• There may be a space-time lag
• Things don't always instantaneously change to reflect the change within you
• This gives you the greatest opportunity to stand firm on the idea of the change you decide you have made

